{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"text","text":"object "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SmartCard"}],"languages":["data"]}]},{"items":[{"attributes":[{"kind":"default","value":"true"}],"type":[{"text":"boolean","kind":"text"}],"required":false,"introducedVersion":"10.12.4","name":"allowSmartCard","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":", the system disables smart cards for logins, authorizations, and screen saver unlocking. It’s still allowed for other functions, such as signing emails and accessing the web. The device requires a restart for a setting change to take effect."}]}]},{"required":false,"introducedVersion":"10.12.4","attributes":[{"value":"0","kind":"default"},{"kind":"allowedValues","values":["0","1","2","3"]}],"type":[{"text":"integer","kind":"text"}],"name":"checkCertificateTrust","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Configures the certificate trust check and has one of the following possible values:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"0"},{"type":"text","text":": Turns off certificate trust check."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1"},{"text":": Turns on certificate trust check. The device performs a standard validity check but doesn’t include additional revocation checks.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"2","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": Turns on certificate trust check. The device also performs a soft revocation check. Until CRL/OCSP explicitly rejects the certificate, the device considers it valid. This setting means that unavailable or unreachable CRL/OCSP allow this check to succeed."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"3","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": Turns on certificate trust check. The device also performs a hard revocation check. Unless CRL/OCSP explicitly says “This certificate is OK,” the device considers it invalid. This option is the most secure."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]},{"introducedVersion":"10.12.4","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", a user can only log in or authenticate with a smart card."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Available: macOS 10.13.2+","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"attributes":[{"kind":"default","value":"false"}],"name":"enforceSmartCard","type":[{"kind":"text","text":"boolean"}],"required":false},{"type":[{"kind":"text","text":"boolean"}],"name":"oneCardPerUser","attributes":[{"kind":"default","value":"false"}],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", a user can pair with only one smart card, although existing pairings are allowed if already set up."}]}],"introducedVersion":"10.12.4","required":false},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1"},{"type":"text","text":", the device enables the screen saver when the user removes the smart card."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Available: macOS 10.13.4+"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"attributes":[{"value":"0","kind":"default"},{"kind":"allowedValues","values":["0","1"]}],"introducedVersion":"10.12.4","type":[{"kind":"text","text":"integer"}],"name":"tokenRemovalAction","required":false},{"introducedVersion":"10.12.4","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", users don’t get the pairing dialog, although existing pairings still work."}]}],"name":"UserPairing","type":[{"kind":"text","text":"boolean"}],"attributes":[{"value":"true","kind":"default"}],"required":false